                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d80">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Denby</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-07-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1113.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    2263 in regard to the antimissionary riots at Chengtu.</p>
                <p>You state that “these riots are inexplicable except on the theory of official
                    connivance.” If the connivance of high Chinese officials in this antiforeign
                    demonstration be reasonably shown, stern reprobation and punishment must be
                    expected, with due reparation and safeguards for the future. You will continue
                    your efforts to elicit the truth, and act accordingly within your standing
                    instructions.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
